# Production image excludes everything not needed at runtime. The Dockerfile
# explicitly COPYs the directories it does need; this file just stops the
# build context from being bloated by source artefacts that would force
# rebuilds on every test edit.

# VCS / IDE
.git
.gitignore
.github
.editorconfig
.cursor
.claude

# Local dev / runtime artefacts
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
node_modules
*/node_modules
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage
*.log

# Tests + spec sources (production image runs the compiled bundle only)
**/__tests__
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx

# Client app — served separately (CDN / static host), not from the server
# image. We must keep `client/package.json` in the build context though:
# the root package.json declares `"workspaces": ["client", "server"]`, so
# `npm ci` needs both workspace manifests to validate the lockfile and
# resolve the workspace tree. Excluding the manifest would fail npm with
# a workspace-resolution error.
client
!client/package.json

# Misc
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
README.md
RUNBOOK.md
*.md
docs
progress
